l Foster appears confused until Det. Alvarez explains that it is the \"Justice Prisoner and Alien Transportation System\". Marshal Foster then confirms the prisoner will be transported via JPATS, however he is really breaking the prisoner out of custody after robbing the police precinct of valuable evidence against a dentist.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt1422565/|title=The Dentist|via=www.imdb.com}}</ref>\n*''[[Orange Is the New Black]]'' (television show) episode \"Thirsty Bird\" (2014), prisoner [[Piper Chapman]] is transported on a JPATS plane for a transfer from Litchfield prison in New York to a Chicago detention facility. US Marshals are shown doing prisoner pat-downs before boarding and then staffing the flight. Prisoners are shown boarding the flight from various locations, including both male and female.\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n{{refbegin}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20080916073926/http://www.ice.gov/partners/dro/airtran.htm U.S. Immigration and Customs Enforcement - Air Transportation]\n{{refend}}\n* Increasing the local use of the US Marshals Service Justice Prisoner and Alien Transportation System (JPATS)/Ingo Remo Johnson (Author), Publisher: Western Baptist College, January 1, 1994, ASIN: B0006RI4HS /  [https://www.amazon.co.uk/Increasing-Marshalls-Service-Prisoner-Transportation/dp/B0006RI4HS Increasing the local use of the US Marshalls Service Justice Prisoner and Alien Transportation System]\n\nOut of Orange:A Memoir \u2013 HarperCollins, May 5, 2015 by Cleary Wolters (Author) {{ISBN|0062376152}}, 9780062376152\n\n== External links ==\n{{Portal|United States|Politics|Aviation}}\n* {{Official website|https://www.usmarshals.gov/jpats}}\n\n\n{{Airlines of the United States}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Justice Prisoner And Alien Transportation System}}\n[[Category:Airlines of the United States]]\n[[Category:Police aviation]]\n[[Category:United States Department of Justice agencies]]\n[[Category:Government 