ose |last=Pontes |publisher=EV Sales |date=27 January 2017 |accessdate=13 February 2018}}</ref>\n| 1,084\n|\n| 346\n| 213\n| 262\n| 229\n| 34\n\n|-\n| align=left | {{DEN}}<ref name=\"Denmark2013_15\">{{cite web|url=http://www.bilimp.dk/statistics/index.asp |title=Statistik |language=Danish |trans-title=Statistics (Passenger cars by model) |author=De Danske Bilimport\u00f8rer |publisher=Bilimp |date=January 2016 |accessdate=28 February 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130508044311/http://www.bilimp.dk/statistics/index.asp |archivedate=8 May 2013 }} ''Select 2015/2014/2013 \u2013 \"Hele \u00e5ret\" for the corresponding year and click on \"Pr. model\" for details of sales by brand and model.''</ref><ref name=\"Denmark2017\">{{cite web |url=https://www.bilimp.dk/Nyhed?id=5855 |title=\u00c5RETS BILSALG 2017 |language=Danish|trans-title=Car sales 2017 |author=De Danske Bilimport\u00f8rer |publisher=Bilimp |date=8 January 2018 |access-date=13 February 2018}} ''Download the file \"12-2017.xls\" and click on the tab \"Pressemeddelelse\"''</ref>\n| 1,077\n|\n| 41\n| 252\n| 645\n| 138\n| 1\n\n|- style=\"background:lightgrey;\"\n| || || || || || ||\n|-\n| style=\"background:#f0f0ff;\" align=left | {{flag|Europe}}<ref name=Sales2013/><ref name=\"BEVtop2014EU\">{{cite press release |url=http://newsroom.nissan-europe.com/EU/en-gb/Media/Media.aspx?mediaid=128573 |title=Nissan LEAF is the best-selling electric car in Europe for fourth year in a row |publisher=Nissan Europe |location=Rolle, Switzerland |date=19 January 2015 |accessdate=28 March 2016}} ''A total of 5,804 all-electric BMW i3s were sold in Europe in 2014. The i3 BEV ranked as the fourth top selling all-electric car in Europe in 2014.''</ref><ref name=\"PHEVtop2015EU\">{{cite web| url=http://europe.autonews.com/article/20160315/ANE/160319949/hybrid-sales-expected-to-triple-in-europe-as-tougher-co2-rules-loom |title=Hybrid sales expected to triple in Europe as tougher CO2 rules loom  |first=Nick |last=Gibbs |work=[[Automotive News|Automotive News Europe]]|date=15 March 2016 |accessdate=28 March 2016}} ''Sales in Europe as reported by [[JATO Dynamics]]: A total of 3,940 BMW i3 REx variants were sold in Europe in 2014, ranking as the third best selling plug-in hybrid in the continent. During 2015 sales totaled 5,481 all-electric BMW i3s and 6,566 i3 REx models (total 12,047).''</ref><ref name=\"Europetop2016\">{{cite web |url=http://ev-sales.blogspot.com.br/2017/01/europe-december-2016.html |title=Europe December 2016 (Updated) |last=Jose |first=Pontes |publisher=EVSales.com |date=30 January 2017 |accessdate=4 February 2018}} '' A total of 15,060 units of both variants of the BMW i3 were sold in Europe in 2016.''</ref><ref name=\"Europe2017\">{{cite web|url=http://ev-sales.blogspot.ca/2018/01/europe-december-2017.html | title=Europe December 2017 | last=Jose | first=Pontes | publisher=EVSales.com| date=28 January 2018 | accessdate=4 February 2018}} '' A total of 20,855 units of both variants of the BMW i3 were sold in Europe in 2017.''</ref><ref name=Europe2018>{{cite web|url=http://ev-sales.blogspot.com/2019/01/europe-december-2018.html| title=Europe December 2018 | last=Jose | first=Pontes | publisher=EVSales.com| date=28 January 2019 | accessdate=28 January 2019}} \"European sales in 2018 totaled 386,347 plug-in passenger cars and about 22,000 light commercial vehicles (vans). The market share of the plug-in car segment was 2.5%\"</ref>\n! style=\"background:#f0f0ff;\"| 83,615\n| style=\"background:#f0f0ff;\"| 24,432\n| style=\"background:#f0f0ff;\"| 20,855\n| style=\"background:#f0f0ff;\"| 15,060\n| style=\"background:#f0f0ff;\"| 12,047\n| style=\"background:#f0f0ff;\"| 9,744\n| style=\"background:#f0f0ff;\"| 1,477\n\n|-\n! style=\"background:#f0f0ff;\"| Global sales<ref name=Sales2013/><ref name=BMWi2014/><ref name=BMWi2015/><ref name=Top10PEVs2016/><ref name=\"BMWi2017\">{{cite press release |url=https://www.press.bmwgroup.com/latin-america-caribb