er=InsideEVs.com|date=15 March 2014|accessdate=18 March 2014}}</ref> the 2014 World Green Car of the Year; the 2014 World Car Design of the Year.,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/jimhenry/2014/04/17/bmwi3-drives-off-with-green-world-car-of-the-year-award-plus-a-surprise/|title=New York Auto Show: BMWi3 Is The 2014 World Green Car Of The Year|author=Jim Henry|work=[[Forbes]]|date=17 April 2014|accessdate=17 April 2014}}</ref> UK Car of the Year 2014, UK Best Super-mini of 2014 and [[Green Car Journal]]'s 2015 [[Green Car of the Year]] Award.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.freep.com/story/money/cars/2014/11/20/green-car-year-bmw/70008216/|title=BMW i3 named 2015 Green Car of the Year|author=Alisa Priddle|work=[[Detroit Free Press]]|date=20 November 2014|accessdate=21 November 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn Australia, the BMW i3 received the 2014 [[Wheels Car of the Year]] by [[Wheels (magazine)|Wheels Magazine]].<ref>{{cite web|title = BMW i3 \u2013 Wheels Car of the Year 2014|url = http://www.wheelsmag.com.au/car-of-the-year/1501/bmw-i3-wheels-car-of-the-year-2014/|accessdate = 15 June 2015}}</ref> In South Africa the i3 received \"Design of the Year\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cars.co.za/motoring_news/bmw-i3---design-of-the-year/42135|title=BMW i3 \u2013 Design of the Year|date=25 January 2016|work=Cars.co.za|access-date=1 November 2017|language=en-US}}</ref> and \"Game Changer of the Year\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cars.co.za/motoring_news/bmw-i3---game-changer-of-the-year/42139|title=BMW i3 \u2013 Game Changer of the Year|date=22 January 2016|work=Cars.co.za|access-date=1 November 2017|language=en-US}}</ref> in 2016 by the automotive website [http://cars.co.za cars.co.za].\n\nAt the [[New York International Auto Show#2017|2017 New York International Auto Show]] the 94 Ah i3 was named the inaugural winner of the \"World Urban Car of the Year\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.press.bmwgroup.com/united-kingdom/article/detail/T0269801EN_GB/the-bmw-i3-94ah-wins-2017-world-urban-car-award|title=The BMW i3 94Ah wins 2017 World Urban Car Award.|website=www.press.bmwgroup.com|accessdate=1 April 2018}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n\n* [[Automatic parking]]\n* [[Electric car use by country]]\n* [[Government incentives for plug-in electric vehicles]]\n* [[List of electric cars currently available]]\n* [[List of modern production plug-in electric vehicles]]\n* [[List of production battery electric vehicles]]\n* [[Personal Urban Mobility and Accessibility]]\n\n==References==\n\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n\n{{Commons category-multi|BMW i3|BMW i3 Concept}}\n* [https://www.bmwusa.com/vehicles/bmwi/i3/ BMW i3 official website]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20130910103548/http://www.bmw.co.uk/en/new-vehicles/bmw-i/i3/2013/start.html BMW i3 UK website]\n* [http://totalcarmagazine.com/newcars/2013/11/11/first_drive_bmw_i3_2013/ BMW i3 road test]\n* [http://carsspyphotos.com/2013-bmw-i3-spied-in-sweden/ BMW i3 (Mega City)- first spy shots]\n* [http://www.torquenews.com/2250/bmw-i3-rex-vs-chevrolet-volt-two-different-approaches-plug-hybrids BMW i3 REx vs. Chevrolet Volt: two different approaches to plug-in hybrids], Torque News, June 2014\n\n; Video\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XEUKrODv_Ds BMW i3. From the first idea to the final car], [[BMW]], July 2014 ([[YouTube]])\n\n{{BMW cars: 2000s to 2010s}}\n{{BMW vehicles}}\n\n[[Category:BMW vehicles|i3]]\n[[Category:City cars]]\n[[Category:Coup\u00e9s]]\n[[Category:Hatchbacks]]\n[[Category:Police vehicles]]\n[[Category:Battery electric cars currently in production]]\n[[Category:Electric car models]]\n[[Category:Electric city cars]]\n[[Category:Cars introduced in 2013]]\n", "name_user": "Lklundin", "label": "safe", "comment": "ce source: website=InsideEVs", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/BMW_i3"}
{"title_page": "List of the oldest schools in the Philippines", "text_new": "{{See also|Dispute over the oldest school in the Philippines}}\n{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{Dynamic list}}\n\n[[File:UST Main Building from the field.JPG|thumb|The [[University of Santo Tomas|Royal and Pontifical University of Santo Tomas]], established by the [[Dominican Order|Dominican missionaries]] in 1611 and raised to the rank of a University in 1645 by [[Pope Innocent X]] through the petition of [[Philip IV of Spain]], is currently the educational institution with the oldest extant University charter in Asia.<ref name=\"rem_rectors1\">{{cite journal |url=http://www.varsitarian.net/circle/remembering_our_rectors |title=Remembering our Rectors |author=Garcia, F.C. |volume=77 |issue=9 |work=[[The Varsitarian]] |date=February 1, 2006 |accessdate=November 9, 2011}}</ref><ref name=Twelve1>De Ramos, N.V., 2000. ''I Walked with Twelve UST Rectors''.</ref>]]\n\nThis is a '''list of educational institutions in the Philippines arranged according to the dates of their foundation'''. It comprises the list of the oldest schools in the [[Philippines]] sorted in various categories, and gives an overview of the development of [[Education in the Philippines|education]] and [[Higher education in the Philippines|higher learning]] in the Philippines. To be included in this list, an institution must satisfy a traditional definition of a formal educational institution at the time of its founding.\n\nThe oldest universities, colleges, [[vocational school]]s and the first modern public education system in Asia were created during the [[History of the Philippines, 1565\u20131898|Spanish colonial period]]. The earliest schools were founded by Spanish [[Catholic missionaries]]. By the time Spain was replaced by the United States as the colonial power, [[Filipinos]] were among the most educated subjects in all of Asia.<ref>{{Harvnb|Coleman|2009|pp=[https://books.google.com/books?id=7oiTkrg9tfUC&pg=PA17 17\u201359]}}</ref>\n\n==Dispute over the oldest school==\n{{Main|Dispute over the oldest school in the Philippines}}\nThe title of the oldest in the Philippines have been topic for [[Dispute over the oldest school in the Philippines|debate between two educational institutions]]: the University of Santo Tomas and the University of San Carlos.<ref name=carolinian>[https://todayscarolinian.net/ust-usc-engages-in-friendly-debate/ UST, USC engages in friendly debate] ''Today's Carolinian'' Accessed 19 April 2020</ref>\n\nThe [[University of Santo Tomas]], established in 1611 as the Colegio de Nuestra Se\u00f1ora de Santisimo Rosario, is generally recognized as the oldest university in the Philippines. In 1935 the Commonwealth government of the Philippines through the Historical Research and Markers Committee declared that UST was \"oldest university under the American flag.\"<ref name=NationalMarkerDatabase>[https://www.hmdb.org/m.asp?m=72333&fbclid=IwAR0v7xr3b8_u9ev64tnBLbK7ihYYMRtJvQeWN9R1kWJmNcxwkzbsCNXVCQg The Historical Marker Database] accessed 19 April 2020</ref> In the 1990s, the [[Intramuros Administration]] installed a marker on the original site of the University of Santo Tomas with the recognition that the university is the \"oldest university in Asia.\"<ref name=MarkerIA>[https://www.hmdb.org/m.asp?m=25286 University of Santo Tomas] ''Intramuros Administration marker'' Accessed 23 April 2020</ref> In 2011 [[Pope Benedict XVI]] recognized UST as \"the oldest institution of Catholic higher education in the Far East,\"<ref name=PopeBenedictXVI>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oBM832jp_8M&t=&fbclid=IwAR1dKm1YEa8rI1Eaotj1fsqTt4B9Fle0cfI18IkvEMu6k7G7akmPsyUoZNY The Papal Message from Pope Benedict XVI to the Pontifical and Royal University of Santo Tomas] accessed 19 April 2020</ref> while in 2012 the [[National Historical Commission of the Philippines]] published an online article recognizing UST as \"Asia\u2019s Oldest University.<ref name=NHCPWebsite>[http://nhcp.gov.ph/asias-oldest-university-the-royal-and-pontifical-university-of-santo-tomas/?fbclid=IwAR1gv4eDnqJlLa-oPyEZxqVT703v7lcF2Nu8E-HoYuGnYTQCTWQckPMiyAs Asia\u2019s Oldest University, The Royal and Pontifical University of Santo Tomas] 'National Historical Commission of the Philippines' accessed 19 April 2020</ref> \n\nHowever, the [[University of San Carlos]] has opposed this recognition and claims that it is older than the University of Santo Tomas by 16 years by tracing its roots to the [[Colegio de San Ildefonso]] (established 1595).<ref name=USCWebsiteHistory>[http://www.usc.edu.ph/about/history About USC] 'The University of San Carlos Website' accessed 19 April 2020</ref> In 1995, the University of San Carlos celebrated its Quadricentennial (400th Anniversary).<ref name=PressReaderTorres>[https://www.pressreader.com/philippines/philippine-daily-inquirer-1109/20110127/282587374438039?fbclid=IwAR1wCKmex5q47jaVgxwRU9ug1-beHJqva6-ZEG-rqgdUa5hKEh_j2EgUvBE No contest: UST is oldest university] 'Philippine Daily Inquirer' Acessed 19 April 2020</ref>\n\nNumerous scholars and official government bodies have reviewed the case. In 2010, the [[National Historical Commission of the Philippines]] installed a bronze marker declaring USC's foundation late in the 18th Century, effectively disproving any direct connection with the [[Colegio de San Ildefonso]]. <ref name=NHCPMarkerforUSC>[https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:University_of_San_Carlos_historical_marker.jpg?fbclid=IwAR0GL9qadNlmmyCym1e5LC76TUuoYYFR-ceFANKqj8bKpudkENbOh3zouwg NHCP historical marker for University of San Carlos in Cebu City] 'National Historical Commission of the Philippines marker' accessed 19 April 2020</ref> According to Dr. Victor Torres of the De La Salle University, the University of San Carlos' claim dates back to 1948 only when USC was declared a University.<ref name=PressReaderTorres/> [[Fidel Villarroel]] from the University of Santo Tomas argued that USC only took over the facility of the former Colegio de San Ildefonso and that there is no 'visible' and 'clear' link between San Carlos and San Ildefonso. <ref name=VarsitarianVillarroel>[https://varsitarian.net/news/20110126/ust_is_oldest_period?fbclid=IwAR1ag_23zvd6jOBirSwro3X7bU7DE2cISdQGwk_K7xn0FzyEVS7yKwHeENA UST is oldest, period] 'The Varsitarian' Accessed 19 April 2020</ref> Aloysius Cartagenas (a Cebuano), in a paper published by Philippiniana Sacra, stated that the correct foundation year of USC is 1867, and not 1595,<ref name=PhilippineEJournal>[https://ejournals.ph/article.php?id=9156&fbclid=IwAR0i59r1M_hHP0yhOjTbHpWptjpC_0XnLONY8iYemgwG2MudibsxGiOV2II Which Is the Oldest University? Revisiting the Conflicting Claims of the University of Santo Tomas,Manila and University of San Carlos, Cebu in Light of the Historyof Seminario (Mayor) de San Carlos of Cebu] 'Philippine E-Journals' accessed 19 April 2020</ref> while in 2012 the [[National Historical Commission of the Philippines]] cemented its previous position when it published an online article recognizing UST as \"Asia\u2019s Oldest University.<ref name=NHCPWebsite/>\n\n==Oldest educational institutions==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:25%;\" | Current name/<br />Latest name before <br />extinction\n! scope=\"col\" | Year<br />founded\n! scope=\"col\" | Name at time of&nbsp;foundation\n! scope=\"col\" | Founding<br />order\n! scope=\"col\" | Location upon foundation/<br />Last location if extinct\n! scope=\"col\" | Current<br />status\n! scope=\"col\" | Current/Last<br />affiliations\n! scope=\"col\" | Type\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | {{abbr|Ref|Reference}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | [[Real Colegio de Santa Potenciana|Colegio de Santa Potenciana]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 1589\n| ''Colegio de Santa Potenciana''\n| [[Franciscan Order]]\n| [[Intramuros]], [[Manila]]\n| style=\"background:#fcc; text-align:center;\" | Defunct\n| \n| [[Private university|Private]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=grant>[http://www.philippinehistory.net/1617santapotenciana.htm Grant to the seminary of Santa Potenciana, 1617] accessed May 30, 2012</ref><ref name=poten>[http://intramuros2007.wordpress.com/2007/02/18/real-colegio-de-santa-potenciana/ Real Colegio de Santa Potenciana] accessed May 30, 2012</ref><ref name=letters>Perez Dasmarinas, Luis. Letters from Luis Perez Dasmari\u00f1as to Felipe II. In The Philippine Islands, 1493-1898. Ohio: A.H. Clark Company, 1903-9. Vol. 9</ref><ref name=edukasyon>[http://filipinocorner.blogspot.com/2010/11/ang-edukasyon-sa-panahon-ng-mga-kastila.html Ang edukasyon sa panahon ng mga Kastila] \"The Filipino Corner\" accessed October 27, 2012</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | [[Universidad de San Ignacio|Colegio de Manila]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 1590\n| ''Colegio de Manila''\n| [[Society of Jesus]]\n| [[Intramuros]], [[Manila]]\n| style=\"background:#fcc; text-align:center;\" | Defunct\n| [[Society of Jesus]]\n| [[Seminary]], [[Pontifical university|Pontifical]], Royal, [[Private university|Private]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=edukasyon/><ref name=\"hundred\">[http://www.ateneo.edu/index.php?p=348 The First Hundred Years of the Ateneo de Manila] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120915093428/http://ateneo.edu/index.php?p=348 |date=2012-09-15 }} ''Ateneo de Manila University website'' May 1, 2012</ref><ref name=\"geo\">[http://www.plm.edu.ph/university-profile/geographical-plm.html Geographical History] ''Pamantasan ng Lungsod ng Maynila website'' May 1, 2012</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | [[Colegio de San Ildefonso]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 1595\n| ''[[Colegio de San Ildefonso]]''\n| [[Society of Jesus]]\n| [[Cebu City]]\n| style=\"background:#fcc; text-align:center;\" | Defunct\n| [[Society of Jesus]]\n| [[Private university|Private]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=edukasyon/><ref name=\"claim\">[http://usc.edu.ph/about_usc/about_usc_usc_history.jsp About USC: University of San Carlos] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120626001638/http://usc.edu.ph/about_usc/about_usc_usc_history.jsp |date=2012-06-26 }} ''University of San Carlos website'' retrieved on 2012-04-24</ref><ref name=torres>[http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/inquirerheadlines/nation/view/20110127-316853/No-contest-UST-is-oldest-university No contest: UST is oldest university] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140301005842/http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/inquirerheadlines/nation/view/20110127-316853/No-contest-UST-is-oldest-university |date=2014-03-01 }} ''Inquirer.net'' accessed May 30, 2012</ref><ref name=char>[http://www.varsitarian.net/news/20110126/ust_is_oldest_period UST is oldest, period] ''Varsitarian website'' accessed May 30, 2012</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | San Jose Seminary\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 1601\n| ''Colegio de San Jose''\n| [[Society of Jesus]]\n| [[Intramuros]], [[Manila]]\n| {{active}}\n| [[Society of Jesus]]\n| [[Private university|Private]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=edukasyon/><ref name=cdsj>[http://sanjoseseminary.org/about-us/history History of Colegio de San Jose / San Jose Seminary] ''San Jose Seminary website'' accessed May 12, 2012</ref><ref name=\"hobbit\">[http://monkshobbit.wordpress.com/2009/10/11/fr-miguel-a-bernad-s-j-colegio-de-san-jose-1601-2001-a-quick-survey-of-the-turbulent-400-year-history-of-an-educational-institution/ Fr. Miguel A. Bernad, S.J.: \"Colegio de San Jos\u00e9 (1601-2001): A Quick Survey of the Turbulent 400-year History of an Educational Institution\"] ''Monk's Hobbit'' May 1, 2012</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | [[University of Santo Tomas]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 1611\n| ''[[University of Santo Tomas|Colegio de Nuestra Se\u00f1ora de Santisimo Rosario]]''\n| [[Dominican Order]]\n| [[Intramuros]], [[Manila]]\n| {{active}}\n| [[Dominican Order]]\n| [[Private university|Private]], [[Pontifical university|Pontifical]], Royal\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=edukasyon/><ref name=\"twentieth19\">{{cite book | last = Lim-Pe | first = Josefina | title = The University of Santo Tomas in the Twentieth Century | publisher = University of Santo Tomas Press, Manila | year = 1973 | pages=1\u201319}}</ref><ref name=ust>[http://www.ust.edu.ph/index.php/history.html History of the University of Santo Tomas] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120302015308/http://www.ust.edu.ph/index.php/history.html |date=2012-03-02 }} ''University of Santo Tomas website'' accessed May 30, 2012</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | [[Colegio de San Juan de Letran|Colegio de Ni\u00f1os Huerfanos de San Juan de Letran]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 1620\n| ''Colegio de Ni\u00f1os Huerfanos de San Juan de Letran''\n| Don Juan Geronimo Guerrero\n| [[Intramuros]], [[Manila]]\n| style=\"background:#fcc; text-align:center;\" | Defunct\n| [[Dominican Order]]\n| [[Private university|Private]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=edukasyon/><ref name=letran>[http://www.letran.edu/main/thecolegio/history/ History of Colegio de San Juan de Letran] ''Colegio de San Juan de Letran website'' accessed May 30, 2012</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Colegio de Huerfanos de San Pedro y San Pablo\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 1620\n| ''Colegio de Huerfanos de San Pedro y San Pablo''\n| [[Dominican Order]]\n| [[Intramuros]], [[Manila]]\n| style=\"background:#fcc; text-align:center;\" | Defunct\n| \n| [[Private university|Private]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=edukasyon/><ref name=letran/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | [[Colegio de San Juan de Letran]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 1630\n| ''Colegio de San Juan de Letran''\n| [[Dominican Order]]\n| [[Intramuros]], [[Manila]]\n| {{active}}\n| [[Dominican Order]]\n| [[Private university|Private]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=edukasyon/><ref name=letran/><ref name=\"link1\">[http://thelance.letran.edu/jun2005/f4_jun2005.htm A Knight's Tale] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080908221123/http://thelance.letran.edu/jun2005/f4_jun2005.htm |date=2008-09-08 }} - The Lance, June 2005</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | [[Santa Isabel College Manila]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 1632\n| ''[[Santa Isabel College Manila|Colegio de Santa Isabel]]''\n| \n| [[Intramuros]], [[Manila]]\n| {{active}}\n| [[Daughters of Charity of Saint Vincent de Paul]]\n| [[Private university|Private]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=edukasyon/><ref name=dc>[http://santaisabel.dcphilippines.org/ Santa Isabel College] ''Santa Isabel College website'' accessed May 28, 2012</ref><ref name=wp>[http://intramuros2007.wordpress.com/2007/02/18/colegio-de-santa-isabel/ Colegio de Santa Isabel] ''intramuros.wordpress.com'' accessed October 27, 2012</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | [[Universidad de San Felipe de Austria]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 1640\n| ''Universidad de San Felipe de Austria''\n| [[Royal Audience of Manila|Audiencia Real de Manila]]\n| [[Intramuros]], [[Manila]]\n| style=\"background:#fcc; text-align:center;\" | Defunct\n| \n| [[Public university|Public]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=edukasyon/><ref name=felipe>[https://www.webcitation.org/5sAqOqPsd?url=http://www.philstar.com/Article.aspx?articleid=533258 The first university] ''The Philippine Star'' accessed May 28, 2012</ref>\n|}\n\n==Oldest educational institutions in continuous operation==\n{{legend2|#99FF99|Disputed|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}{{efn|name=sancarlosfn1}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:25%;\" | Current name\n! scope=\"col\" | Traces origin to\n! scope=\"col\" | Year<br />founded\n! scope=\"col\" | Founding<br />order\n! scope=\"col\" | Location upon foundation\n! scope=\"col\" | Type\n! scope=\"col\" | Current<br />affiliations\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | {{abbr|Ref|Reference}}\n|- style=\"background:#9f9;\"\n! scope=\"row\" | [[University of San