elist-lr|refs=\n{{efn-lr|name=centroescolarfn1|\n[[Centro Escolar University]] was established as Centro Escolar de Se\u00f1oritas by Do\u00f1a [[Librada Avelino]] and Do\u00f1a [[Carmen de Luna]] in 1907 to cater the young women of [[Manila]]. The university is still continuously operating, but now as a co-educational institution.\n}}\n}}\n|}\n\n==Oldest public educational institutions==\n{{legend2|#F9F9F9|Still in operation|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#ffbbbb|Defunct|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:25%;\" | Current name\n! scope=\"col\" | Year<br />founded\n! scope=\"col\" | Name at time of&nbsp;foundation\n! scope=\"col\" | Location upon foundation\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | {{abbr|Ref|Reference}}\n|- style=\"background:#ffbbbb;\"\n! scope=\"row\" | [[Universidad de San Felipe de Austria]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 1640\n| Universidad de San Felipe de Austria\n| [[Intramuros]], [[Manila]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=felipe/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | [[Philippine Merchant Marine Academy]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 1820\n| Escuela Nautica de Manila\n| [[Zambales]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=pmma>[https://www.pmma.edu.ph/about-pmma/ About Philippine Merchant Marine Academy] 'Philippine Marine Merchant Academy website'</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | [[Don Honorio Ventura Technological State University]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 1861\n| Escuela De Artes y Oficios De Bacolor\n| [[Pampanga]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=dhvtsu>[http://www.dhvsu.edu.ph/index.php/dhvsu/history History] 'Don Honorio Ventura Technological State University website'</ref>\n|}\n\n==Educational institutions with the oldest university charters==\n{{legend2|#F9F9F9|Still in operation|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#ffbbbb|Defunct|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! scope=