/mham.edu.ph/wp/mhammedicine/ Matias H. Aznar Memorial College of Medicine] ''Matias H. Aznar Memorial College of Medicine website'' Accessed 19 April 2020</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Manila Central University College of Medicine\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 1947\n| [[Manila Central University]]\n| [[Manila]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=MCUMed>[http://www.mcu.edu.ph/stag/?page_id=8712 A Rich History and Track Record of Success] ''Manila Central University website'' Accessed 19 April 2020</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | FEU Institute of Medicine - [[Nicanor Reyes Medical Foundation]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 1952\n| [[Far Eastern University]]\n| [[Manila]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=FEUMed>[https://www.feu-nrmf.ph/im/about.php History of the Far Eastern University Institute of Medicine] ''Far Eastern University Institute of Medicine website'' Accessed 19 April 2020</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | [[UERMMMC College of Medicine]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 1956\n| [[University of the East]]\n| [[Manila]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=UERMMMCMed>[https://uerm.edu.ph/aboutus/history History of the University of the East Rammon Magsaysay Memorial Medical Center] ''University of the East Ramon Magsaysay Memorial Medical Center website'' Accessed 19 April 2020</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | [[Cebu Institute of Medicine]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 1957\n| [[Cebu Institute of Medicine]]\n| [[Cebu]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=CIMMed>[http://cim.edu.ph/about-us/ About us] ''Cebu Institute of Medicine website'' Accessed 19 April 2020</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Lyceum Northwestern University Dr. Francisco Q. Duque Medical Foundation\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 1974\n| [[Lyceum-Northwestern University]]\n| [[Pangasinan]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=LyceumMed>[https://lyceum.edu.ph/history/ History of the Lyceum-Northwestern University] ''Lyceum-Northwestern University website'' Accessed 19 April 2020</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | West Visayas State University College of Medicine\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 1975\n| [[West Visayas State University]]\n| [[Iloilo]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=WVSMed>[https://wvsu.edu.ph/history/ History] ''West Visayas State University website'' Accessed 19 April 2020</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Virgen Milagrosa University Foundation College of Medicine\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 1975\n| [[Virgen Milagrosa University Foundation]]\n| [[Pangasinan]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=VMUMed>[http://www.vmuf.edu.ph/# Virgen Milagrosa University Foundation College of Medicine] ''Virgen Milagrosa University Foundation College of Medicine website'' Accessed 19 April 2020</ref>\n|}\n\n==Oldest normal schools==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Current name\n! scope=\"col\" | Year<br />founded\n! scope=\"col\" | Name at time of&nbsp;foundation\n! scope=\"col\" | Location upon foundation\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | {{abbr|Ref|Reference}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | [[Universidad de Sta. Isabel]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 1875\n| Escuela Normal de Maestras of Colegio de Sta. Isabel\n| Camarines Sur\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=usinaga>[https://www.usi.edu.ph/Inside%20USI/USIONE_History.html Milestones in the History of One USI] ''Universidad de Sta. Isabel website'' Accessed 19 April 2020</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | [[Philippine Normal University]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 1901\n| Philippine Normal School\n| Manila\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=pnumanila>[https://www.pnu.edu.ph/about-pnu/history-and-milestone/ History and Milestone A Brief History of the Philippine Normal University] ''Philippine Normal University website'' Accessed 19 April 2020</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | [[West Visayas State University]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 1902\n| Iloilo Normal School\n| Iloilo\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=wvsu>[https://wvsu.edu.ph/history/ History] ''West Visayas State University'' Accessed 19 April 2020</ref>\n|}\n\n==Oldest schools of engineering==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Name\n! scope=\"col\" | Year<br />founded\n! scope=\"col\" | Educational institution\n! scope=\"col\" | Location upon foundation\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | {{abbr|Ref|Reference}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | [[University of Santo Tomas Faculty of Engineering]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 1907\n| [[University of Santo Tomas]]\n| [[Intramuros]], [[Manila]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref>[https://www.bulsu.edu.ph/about/history] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120525044736/http://www.ust.edu.ph/index.php/undergraduate-programs/76-faculty-of-engineering.html |date=2012-05-25 }} ''University of Santo Tomas website'' accessed July 31, 2012</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | [[Map\u00faa University]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 1925\n| [[Map\u00faa University]]\n| [[Manila]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=mapuached>[https://ched.gov.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Mapua-University.pdf Mapua University] Commission on Higher Education</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Education in the Philippines]]\n** [[Education in the Philippines during Spanish rule]]\n** [[Education in the Philippines during the American rule]]\n* [[Higher education in the Philippines]]\n** [[Medical education in the Philippines]]\n** [[Legal education in the Philippines]]\n** [[List of universities and colleges in the Philippines]]\n** [[List of Catholic universities and colleges in the Philippines]]\n\n{{Lists of European universities and colleges by era}}\n{{Spanish Colonial architecture}}\n{{Spanish Empire}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Oldest schools}}\n[[Category:Education in the Philippines]]\n[[Category:Lists of schools in the Philippines]]\n[[Category:Lists of oldest buildings and structures|Philippines]]\n[[Category:Lists of education-related superlatives]]\n[[Category:Lists of oldest schools]]\n", "text_old": "{{See also|Dispute over the oldest school in the Philippines}}\n{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{Dynamic list}}\n\n[[File:UST Main Building from the field.JPG|thumb|The [[University of Santo Tomas|Royal and Pontifical University of Santo Tomas]], established by the [[Dominican Order|Dominican missionaries]] in 1611 and raised to the rank of a University in 1645 by [[Pope Innocent X]] through the petition of [[Philip IV of Spain]], is currently the educational institution with the oldest extant University charter in Asia.<ref name=\"rem_rectors1\">{{cite journal |url=http://www.varsitarian.net/circle/remembering_our_rectors |title=Remembering our Rectors |author=Garcia, F.C. |volume=77 |issue=9 |work=[[The Varsitarian]] |date=February 1, 2006 |accessdate=November 9, 2011}}</ref><ref name=Twelve1>De Ramos, N.V., 2000. ''I Walked with Twelve UST Rectors''.</ref>]]\n\nThis is a '''list of educational institutions in the Philippines arranged according to the dates of their foundation'''. It comprises the list of the oldest schools in the [[Philippines]] sorted in various categories, and gives an overview of the development of [[Education in the Philippines|education]] and [[Higher education in the Philippines|higher learning]] in the Philippines. To be included in this list, an institution must satisfy a traditional definition of a formal educational institution at the time of its founding.\n\nThe oldest universities, colleges, [[vocational school]]s and the first modern public education system in Asia were created during the [[History of the Philippines, 1565\u20131898|Spanish colonial period]]. The earliest schools were founded by Spanish [[Catholic missionaries]]. By the time Spain was replaced by the United States as the colonial power, [[Filipinos]] were among the most educated subjects in all of Asia.<ref>{{Harvnb|Coleman|2009|pp=[https://books.google.com/books?id=7oiTkrg9tfUC&pg=PA17 17\u201359]}}</ref>\n\n==Dispute over the oldest school==\n{{Main|Dispute over the oldest school in the Philippines}}\nThe title of the oldest in the Philippines have been topic for [[Dispute over the oldest school in the Philippines|debate between two educational institutions]]: the University of Santo Tomas and the University of San Carlos.<ref name=carolinian>[https://todayscarolinian.net/ust-usc-engages-in-friendly-debate/ UST, USC engages in friendly debate] ''Today's Carolinian'' Accessed 19 April 2020</ref>\n\nThe [[University of Santo Tomas]], established in 1611 as the Colegio de Nuestra Se\u00f1ora de Santisimo Rosario, is generally recognized as the oldest university in the Philippines. In 1935 the Commonwealth government of the Philippines through the Historical Research and Markers Committee declared that UST was \"oldest university under the American flag.\"<ref name=NationalMarkerDatabase>[https://www.hmdb.org/m.asp?m=72333&fbclid=IwAR0v7xr3b8_u9ev64tnBLbK7ihYYMRtJvQeWN9R1kWJmNcxwkzbsCNXVCQg The Historical Marker Database] accessed 19 April 2020</ref> In the 1990s, the [[Intramuros Administration]] installed a marker on the original site of the University of Santo Tomas with the recognition that the university is the \"oldest university in Asia.\"<ref name=MarkerIA>[https://www.hmdb.org/m.asp?m=25286 University of Santo Tomas] ''Intramuros Administration marker'' Accessed 23 April 2020</ref> In 2011 [[Pope Benedict XVI]] recognized UST as the \"the oldest institution of Catholic higher education in the Far East,\"<ref name=PopeBenedictXVI>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oBM832jp_8M&t=&fbclid=IwAR1dKm1YEa8rI1Eaotj1fsqTt4B9Fle0cfI18IkvEMu6k7G7akmPsyUoZNY The Papal Message from Pope Benedict XVI to the Pontifical and Royal University of Santo Tomas] accessed 19 April 2020</ref> while in 2012 the [[National Historical Commission of the Philippines]] published an online article recognizing UST as \"Asia\u2019s Oldest University.<ref name=NHCPWebsite>[http://nhcp.gov.ph/asias-oldest-university-the-royal-and-pontifical-university-of-santo-tomas/?fbclid=IwAR1gv4eDnqJlLa-oPyEZxqVT703v7lcF2Nu8E-HoYuGnYTQCTWQckPMiyAs Asia\u2019s Oldest University, The Royal and Pontifical University of Santo Tomas] 'National Historical Commission of the Philippines' accessed 19 April 2020</ref> \n\nHowever, the [[University of San Carlos]] has opposed this recognition and claims that it is older than the University of Santo Tomas by 16 years by tracing its roots to the [[Colegio de San Ildefonso]] (established 1595).<ref name=USCWebsiteHistory>[http://www.usc.edu.ph/about/history About USC] 'The University of San Carlos Website' accessed 19 April 2020</ref> In 1995, the University of San Carlos celebrated its Quadricentennial (400th Anniversary).<ref name=PressReaderTorres>[https://www.pressreader.com/philippines/philippine-daily-inquirer-1109/20110127/282587374438039?fbclid=IwAR1wCKmex5q47jaVgxwRU9ug1-beHJqva6-ZEG-rqgdUa5hKEh_j2EgUvBE No contest: UST is oldest university] 'Philippine Daily Inquirer' Acessed 19 April 2020</ref>\n\nNumerous scholars and official government bodies have reviewed the case. In 2010, the [[National Historical Commission of the Philippines]] installed a bronze marker declaring USC's foundation late in the 18th Century, effectively disproving any direct connection with the [[Colegio de San Ildefonso]]. <ref name=NHCPMarkerforUSC>[https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:University_of_San_Carlos_historical_marker.jpg?fbclid=IwAR0GL9qadNlmmyCym1e5LC76TUuoYYFR-ceFANKqj8bKpudkENbOh3zouwg NHCP historical marker for University of San Carlos in Cebu City] 'National Historical Commission of the Philippines marker' accessed 19 April 2020</ref> According to Dr. Victor Torres of the De La Salle University, the University of San Carlos' claim dates back to 1948 only when USC was declared a University.<ref name=PressReaderTorres/> [[Fidel Villarroel]] from the University of Santo Tomas argued that USC only took over the facility of the former Colegio de San Ildefonso and that there is no 'visible' and 'clear' link between San Carlos and San Ildefonso. <ref name=VarsitarianVillarroel>[https://varsitarian.net/news/20110126/ust_is_oldest_period?fbclid=IwAR1ag_23zvd6jOBirSwro3X7bU7DE2cISdQGwk_K7xn0FzyEVS7yKwHeENA UST is oldest, period] 'The Varsitarian' Accessed 19 April 2020</ref> Aloysius Cartagenas (a Cebuano), in a paper published by Philippiniana Sacra, stated that the correct foundation year of USC is 1867, and not 1595,<ref name=PhilippineEJournal>[https://ejournals.ph/article.php?id=9156&fbclid=IwAR0i59r1M_hHP0yhOjTbHpWptjpC_0XnLONY8iYemgwG2MudibsxGiOV2II Which Is the Oldest University? Revisiting the Conflicting Claims of the University of Santo Tomas,Manila and University of San Carlos, Cebu in Light of the Historyof Seminario (Mayor) de San Carlos of Cebu] 'Philippine E-Journals' accessed 19 April 2020</ref> while in 2012 the [[National Historical Commission of the Philippines]] cemented its previous position when it published an online article recognizing UST as \"Asia\u2019s Oldest University.<ref name=NHCPWebsite/>\n\n==Oldest educational institutions==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:25%;\" | Current name/<br />Latest name before <br />extinction\n! scope=\"col\" | Year<br />founded\n! scope=\"col\" | Name at time of&nbsp;foundation\n! scope=\"col\" | Founding<br />order\n! scope=\"col\" | Location upon foundation/<br />Last location if extinct\n! scope=\"col\" | Current<br />status\n! scope=\"col\" | Current/Last<br />affiliations\n! scope=\"col\" | Type\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | {{abbr|Ref|Reference}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | [[Real Colegio de Santa Potenciana|Colegio de Santa Potenciana]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 1589\n| ''Colegio de Santa Potenciana''\n| [[Franciscan Order]]\n| [[Intramuros]], [[Manila]]\n| style=\"background:#fcc; text-align:center;\" | Defunct\n| \n| [[Private university|Private]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=grant>[http://www.philippinehistory.net/1617santapotenciana.htm Grant to the seminary of Santa Potenciana, 1617] accessed May 30, 2012</ref><ref name=poten>[http://intramuros2007.wordpress.com/2007/02/18/real-colegio-de-santa-potenciana/ Real Colegio de Santa Potenciana] accessed May 30, 2012</ref><ref name=letters>Perez Dasmarinas, Luis. Letters from Luis Perez Dasmari\u00f1as to Felipe II. In The Philippine Islands, 1493-1898. Ohio: A.H. Clark Company, 1903-9. Vol. 9</ref><ref name=edukasyon>[http://filipinocorner.blogspot.com/2010/11/ang-edukasyon-sa-panahon-ng-mga-kastila.html Ang edukasyon sa panahon ng mga Kastila] \"The Filipino Corner\" accessed October 27, 2012</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | [[Universidad de San Ignacio|Colegio de Manila]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 1590\n| ''Colegio de Manila''\n| [[Society of Jesus]]\n| [[Intramuros]], [[Manila]]\n| style=\"background:#fcc; text-align:center;\" | Defunct\n| [[Society of Jesus]]\n| [[Seminary]], [[Pontifical university|Pontifical]], Royal, [[Private university|Private]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=edukasyon/><ref name=\"hundred\">[http://www.ateneo.edu/index.php?p=348 The First Hundred Years of the Ateneo de Manila] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120915093428/http://ateneo.edu/index.php?p=348 |date=2012-09-15 }} ''Ateneo de Manila University website'' May 1, 2012</ref><ref name=\"geo\">[http://www.plm.edu.ph/university-profile/geographical-plm.html Geographical History] ''Pamantasan ng Lungsod ng Maynila website'' May 1, 2012</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | [[Colegio de San Ildefonso]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 1595\n| ''[[Colegio de San Ildefonso]]''\n| [[Society of Jesus]]\n| [[Cebu City]]\n| style=\"background:#fcc; text-align:center;\" | Defunct\n| [[Society of Jesus]]\n| [[Private university|Private]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" 