 San Pablo\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 1822\n| [[Dominican Order]]\n| [[Vigan]]\n| [[Seminary]]\n| [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Nueva Segovia|Archdiocese of Nueva Segovia]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=icst>[http://www.icstvigan.org.ph/ABOUT_ICST/HISTORY.html Immaculate Conception School of Theology history] ''Immaculate Conception School of Theology website'' accessed May 28, 2012</ref><ref name=clar>[http://claretianpublications.com/index.php/diocese/548-archdiocese-of-nueva-segovia Archdiocese of Nueva Segovia] ''Claretian Publications website'' accessed October 28, 2012</ref><ref name=uca>[http://www.ucanews.com/diocesan-directory/html/dps-pr_nueva_segovia_seminary.html Seminaries, Houses of Formation] ''UCA News website'' accessed October 28, 2012</ref><ref name=nsc>[http://nschancery.wordpress.com/about/ Nueva Segovia Chancery directory] ''Nueva Segovia Chancery website'' accessed October 28, 2012</ref>\n|- class=\"sortbottom\"\n! scope=\"row\" colspan=\"8\" style=\"border-top-style:double; font-size:95%;\" | \n; Notes\n{{notelist|refs=\n{{efn|name=sancarlosfn1|\nThe [[University of San Carlos]] traces its roots to the Colegio de San Ildefonso founded by the Spanish Jesuits fathers Antonio Sedeno, Pedro Chirino and Antonio Pereira in 1595, thus claiming to be the oldest still existing school in Asia.<ref name=\"usc\">[http://www.usc.edu.ph/about_usc/about_usc_usc_history.jsp ''University of San Carlos Website''] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120511161241/http://usc.edu.ph/about_usc/about_usc_usc_history.jsp |date=2012-05-11 }}. ''University of San Carlos Website'' May 1, 2012.</ref> USC celebrated its quadricentennial in 1995.<ref name=\"usc\"/> However, this claim is opposed by the [[Pontifical University|Pontifical]] and [[Royal Patronage|Royal]] [[University of Santo Tomas]], which argues that USC only took over the facility of the former Colegio de San Ildefonso and that there is no 'visible' and 'clear' link between San Carlos and San Ildefonso.<ref name=\"inquirer\">[http://opinion.inquirer.net/inquireropinion/columns/view/20110127-316853/No-contest-UST-is-oldest-university ''No Contest, UST is Oldest''] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131111195911/http://opinion.inquirer.net/inquireropinion/columns/view/20110127-316853/No-contest-UST-is-oldest-university |date=2013-11-11 }}. ''Inquirer Website'' May 1, 2012.</ref><ref name=\"varsitarian\">[http://www.varsitarian.net/news/20110126/ust_is_oldest_period ''UST is oldest, period'']. ''Varsitarian Website'' May 1, 2012.</ref>\n\nNotable scholars including Dr. Jose Victor Torres, professor of history at the De La Salle University,<ref name=\"inquirer\"/><ref name=\"montage\">[http://www.montagemagazine.net/jose-victor-torres-dramatizing-history-and-historicizing-drama ''Jose Victor Torres: Dramatizing History and Historicizing Drama''] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130925132420/http://www.montagemagazine.net/jose-victor-torres-dramatizing-history-and-historicizing-drama |date=2013-09-25 }}. ''Montagemagazine Website'' May 1, 2012.</ref> Fr. Aloysius Cartagenas STD, professor at the Seminario Mayor de San Carlos of Cebu<ref name=\"link\">[https://archive.is/20121129182754/http://ph.linkedin.com/pub/aloysius-cartagenas/19/278/81a ''Aloysius Cartagenas'']. ''linkedin.com'' May 1, 2012.</ref><ref name=\"professor\">[https://archive.is/20121221065548/http://www.moic.smsc.edu.ph/school-of-theology/professors-1 ''SMSC Faculty Roster'']. ''Seminario Mayor de San Carlos'' May 1, 2012.</ref> and Fr. [[Fidel Villarroel]], OP, eminent historian and former archivist of Santo Tomas<ref name=\"varsitarian\"/><ref name=\"blogspotr\">[http://azheepineda.blogspot.com/2010/01/ust-archives-director-fr-fidel.html ''UST Archives Director Fr. Fidel'']. ''Fidel Villarroel'' May 1, 2012.</ref><ref name=\"net\">[http://lifestyle.inquirer.net/32045/2-volume-ust-history-charts-evolution-of-higher-education-in-the-philippines ''Evolution of Higher Education in the Philippines'']. ''Inquirer.net'' May 1, 2012.</ref> have also questioned San Carlos' claim of tracing its roots to the 16th Century Colegio de San Ildefonso.<ref name=\"inquirer\"/>\n}}\n}}\n|}\n\n==Oldest educational institutions for girls==\n{{legend2|#F9F9F9|Still in operation|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#ffbbbb|Defunct|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#99FF99|Established as a School for Girls|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:25%;\" | Current name\n! scope=\"col\" | Year<br />founded\n! scope=\"col\" | Name at time of&nbsp;foundation\n! scope=\"col\" | Founding<br />order\n! scope=\"col\" | Location upon foundation\n! scope=\"col\" | Type\n! scope=\"col\" | Current<br />affiliations\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | {{abbr|Ref|Reference}}\n|- style=\"background:#ffbbbb;\"\n! scope=\"row\" | [[Real Colegio de Santa Potenciana|Colegio de Santa Potenciana]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 1589\n| Colegio de Santa Potenciana\n| [[Franciscan Order]]\n| [[Intramuros]], [[Manila]]\n| [[Private university|Private]]\n| \n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=grant/><ref name=poten/><ref name=letters/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | [[Santa Isabel College Manila]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 1632\n| Colegio de Santa Isabel\n| \n| [[Intramuros]], [[Manila]]\n| [[Private university|Private]]\n| [[Daughters of Charity of Saint Vincent de Paul|Daughters of Charity]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=edukasyon/><ref name=dc/><ref name=wp/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Santa Catalina College\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 1706\n| Beaterio Colegio de Santa Catalina de Siena\n| [[Dominican Order]]\n| [[Intramuros]], [[Manila]]\n| [[Private university|Private]]\n| [[Dominican Order]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=edukasyon/><ref name=rosa/><ref name=br/><ref name=fi/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Colegio de Santa Rosa\n| styl